479
00:30:03,968 --> 00:30:07,931
He's now a five-year-old
walking body of big data.

480
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,560
By the way, I've always been curious.

481
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:15,814
What's your connection to Prosecutor Doh?

482
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:19,025
I even heard you call him
by his name from time to time.

483
00:30:19,526 --> 00:30:21,569
Why are you trying to find out about that?

484
00:30:30,078 --> 00:30:31,037
Stop.

485
00:30:43,216 --> 00:30:44,425
Are you MC Sang-ki?

486
00:30:55,061 --> 00:30:56,479
Why are you taking him away?

487
00:30:57,397 --> 00:30:58,773
He's not the culprit.

488
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:00,316
That's what my hunch says.

489
00:31:01,609 --> 00:31:02,527
Come with me.

490
00:31:31,973 --> 00:31:32,891
I knew it.

491
00:31:33,474 --> 00:31:37,437
So Prosecutor Doh led you
to the path of a military investigator.

492
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:41,482
Yes, I tried to go to law school
to become a military prosecutor like him,

493
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:42,984
but I was not competent enough.

494
00:31:43,484 --> 00:31:46,237
And I got crazy nosebleeds
to become a military investigator.

495
00:31:46,738 --> 00:31:49,282
Though that nosebleed
made me who I am now.

496
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:51,451
What? Your nose is bleeding now.

497
00:31:52,285 --> 00:31:54,746
-What? My nose is bleeding? Now?
-Yes.

498
00:31:54,829 --> 00:31:56,539
-Lift your head.
-That can't be.

499
00:31:57,123 --> 00:32:00,585
This nosebleed brings back memories.
I guess I am overworked these days.

500
00:32:00,668 --> 00:32:02,045
Yes, you worked too much.

501
00:32:02,128 --> 00:32:04,505
-Do you have a tissue?
-Yes, I'll get you some.

