00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,111
By the way,

516
00:33:09,654 --> 00:33:12,448
is there a reason
why you rushed this contract?

517
00:33:13,032 --> 00:33:15,618
I must get rid of Noh Hwa-young…

518
00:33:16,953 --> 00:33:21,249
by using this contract for new weapons.

519
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:25,586
What?

520
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:28,131
What's this about, all of a sudden…

521
00:33:28,715 --> 00:33:33,344
CEO Yong, I will help you
with everything I can so you can take IM

522
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:36,180
from Noh Hwa-young completely.

523
00:33:38,307 --> 00:33:39,308
Thank you so much.

524
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:42,103
I will serve you with my utmost loyalty.

525
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:46,024
If there has to be someone above me,
it only has to be you, Minister.

526
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:51,029
Next is about
the Ministry of National Defense.

527
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:54,407
The MND signed an MOU
for a new weapon project

528
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:58,745
with the consortium
of Kang's Solution and IM Defense.

529
00:33:58,828 --> 00:34:01,789
Through this MOU,
Kang's Solution and IM Defense

530
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:04,625
will receive orders
for main projects that will be financed

531
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:06,627
with 10% of the national defense budget

532
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:08,755
to start working
on the new weapons project.

533
00:34:08,838 --> 00:34:10,089
Until now…

534
00:34:18,056 --> 00:34:19,640
NOH HWA-YOUNG

535
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:29,108
So you're calling after watching the news.

536
00:34:29,192 --> 00:34:31,861
Why should I hear about that
through the news?

537
00:34:31,944 --> 00:34:35,907
I was actually going to
visit you and explain it to you soon.

538
00:34:35,990 --> 00:34:39,077
You will have to give me a clear
and plausible explanation.

539
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:43,164
Don't worry, General.
You're going to understand it right away.

540
00:34:49,837 --> 00:34:52,715
Personnel at the MND said this MOU will…

541
00:34:52,799 --> 00:34:56,844
Yong moon-goo, CEO Kang,
and Lee Jae-sik signed that.

542
00:34:56,928 --> 00:35:00,056
It's a clear sign of internal conflict
in the Patriotic Society.

543
00:35:00,139 --> 00:35:03,226
Hong Moo-seob got kicked out,
so the servicepeople

544
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:06,562
of the Patriotic Society will choose
either Lee Jae-sik or Noh Hwa-young

545
00:35:06,646 --> 00:35:08,481
and start a war of loyalty.

546
00:35:09,148 --> 00:35:11,734
It's important to identify friends
or foes in a war.

547
00:35:11,818 --> 00:35:15,113
And there is someone
who's now in a difficult situation.

548
00:35:15,947 --> 00:35:17,532
Vice Corps Commander Heo Kang-in.

549
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:20,243
Want me to tell you why I am above you?

550
00:35:20,326 --> 00:35:21,828
It's simple.

551
00:35:21,911 --> 00:35:24,580
It's because I'm a stronger
serviceperson than you.

552
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:29,627
A symbol of incompetent servicepeople
with male chauvinism.

553
00:35:30,586 --> 00:35:32,672
He put on his uniform
with the strong belief

554
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,674
that he will never take orders from women,

555
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:37,593
but now, he's being trampled
by a woman's military boots.

556
00:35:39,053 --> 00:35:40,429
What happened, Minister?

557
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:44,892
He's been holding onto the line
called Hong Moo-seob to survive until now,

558
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:47,019
but with that line gone now,

559
00:35:47,770 --> 00:35:49,772
his entire military career is at risk.

560
00:35:50,898 --> 00:35:52,817
He's being looked down on
by Noh Hwa-young,

561
00:35:53,442 --> 00:35:55,862
and he's still not acknowledged
by Lee Jae-sik.

562
00:35:57,697 --> 00:36:00,491
I'm going to use Heo Kang-in as the bait.

563
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:03,244
The bait?

564
00:36:05,246 --> 00:36:06,455
He's not a game?

565
00:36:06,539 --> 00:36:08,374
Heo Kang-in is a bait.

566
00:36:08,457 --> 00:36:10,459
A bait to catch a big fish.

567
00:36:11,043 --> 00:36:12,712
Yes, that sounds all right.

568
00:36:13,462 --> 00:36:15,840
Since Yong Moon-goo
is after the X-files right now,

569
00:36:16,465 --> 00:36:18,676
we need something big, too.

570
00:36:19,969 --> 00:36:22,346
Let's finish Private First
Class Pyeon's trial first,

571
00:36:24,098 --> 00:36:26,100
and catch a big fish with the bait.

572
00:36:41,532 --> 00:36:42,617
Military Prosecutor.

573
00:36:45,661 --> 00:36:48,539
Can I see my son one more time, please?

574
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:52,543
I have to give these to him, but I can't.

575
00:36:53,502 --> 00:36:56,631
I've been waiting for you two to come.

576
00:36:57,715 --> 00:36:58,758
Please, I beg you.

577
00:36:59,717 --> 00:37:01,761
My son has bad eyesight.

578
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:04,805
I beg you.

579
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:08,809
I understand how you feel,

580
00:37:09,810 --> 00:37:10,937
but it's a bit tricky to

581
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:12,772
meet the defendant's mother repeatedly

582
00:37:13,606 --> 00:37:14,774
right before the trial.

583
00:37:16,108 --> 00:37:17,151
I'm sorry.

584
00:37:32,166 --> 00:37:35,002
You do the second interrogation
on Private First Class Pyeon.

585
00:37:35,086 --> 00:37:36,879
I have to go to
the Division Commander's office to report.

586
00:37:36,963 --> 00:37:38,422
Yes, sir.

587
00:37:38,506 --> 00:37:39,715
By the way…

588
00:37:40,883 --> 00:37:45,846
You let him meet his mother last time,
but why did you refuse this time?

589
00:37:47,890 --> 00:37:51,352
-That's…
-His mother did nothing wrong.

590
00:37:52,478 --> 00:37:53,646
I know how you feel,

591
00:37:54,730 --> 00:37:56,232
but let's stop being emotional.

592
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:01,654
Yes, sir.

593
00:38:22,216 --> 00:38:24,010
I'll give these to him.

594
00:38:25,219 --> 00:38:26,220
Really?

595
00:38:28,097 --> 00:38:30,057
Thank you.

596
00:38:31,809 --> 00:38:33,227
I can't thank you enough.

597
00:38:35,146 --> 00:38:35,980
Thank you.

598
00:38:58,377 --> 00:39:00,963
I just got the report
from the Staff Judge Advocate

599
00:39:01,589 --> 00:39:03,382
about all of the surviving soldiers

600
00:39:03,466 --> 00:39:06,635
giving the same testimony,
stating there was no abuse.

601
00:39:07,303 --> 00:39:08,220
Yes, ma'am.

602
00:39:08,304 --> 00:39:10,056
What did Private Noh Tae-nam say?

603
00:39:10,139 --> 00:39:11,932
He testified that there was no cruelty.

604
00:39:13,768 --> 00:39:14,894
I see.

605
00:39:14,977 --> 00:39:17,063
Is the suspect giving the same testimony?

606
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:19,607
Prosecutor Cha is
doing an additional interrogation.

607
00:39:21,984 --> 00:39:22,985
Additional?

608
00:39:23,652 --> 00:39:26,947
Is it because you think
there was cruelty or other reasons?

609
00:39:27,031 --> 00:39:31,243
It's the office of justice's plan
to investigate more meticulously.

610
00:39:32,078 --> 00:39:32,912
Really?

611
00:39:43,589 --> 00:39:45,466
-Doh Bae-man.
-Captain Doh Bae-man.

612
00:39:45,966 --> 00:39:48,010
Do you think you'll be able
to argue with me,

613
00:39:48,094 --> 00:39:51,472
asking me if I see this case
as a mother or a division commander?

614
00:39:53,307 --> 00:39:56,185
As for this case, I'm a mother
of a soldier who's a victim.

615
00:39:57,520 --> 00:40:01,440
My son survived but he's in deep shock.

616
00:40:02,525 --> 00:40:05,945
Don't dig into the pain
of the surviving soldiers anymore.

617
00:40:06,904 --> 00:40:08,280
You need to keep that in mind.

618
00:40:17,581 --> 00:40:18,416
Have a seat.

619
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:31,303
Your mother told me to give them to you.

620
00:40:32,346 --> 00:40:33,180
Now…

621
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:37,226
you won't be able to see your mother
until the trial begins.

622
00:40:38,185 --> 00:40:40,771
Is it okay for me to take these?

623
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:42,690
Put them on.

624
00:40:43,691 --> 00:40:45,901
Your mother tried very hard
to give them to you.

625
00:40:56,704 --> 00:40:58,497
How can I even dare to wear these?

626
00:41:06,297 --> 00:41:07,339
Those glasses…

627
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:09,175
when were they broken?

628
00:41:11,844 --> 00:41:13,345
That's not a difficult question.

629
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:15,931
Why can't you answer it?

630
00:41:17,433 --> 00:41:19,560
It looks like someone
broke them on purpose.

631
00:41:21,061 --> 00:41:21,937
Or…

632
00:41:22,021 --> 00:41:25,191
did it get broken
and you had to tape them back?

633
00:41:27,109 --> 00:41:27,943
Yes.

634
00:41:29,820 --> 00:41:30,863
They were broken…

635
00:41:32,698 --> 00:41:34,074
but Tae-nam fixed them for me.

636
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:36,327
Noh Tae-nam did?

637
00:41:36,410 --> 00:41:38,204
Were you close
to Private First Class Pyeon?

638
00:41:38,787 --> 00:41:41,415
The record shows
that he's your direct superior.

639
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:42,625
No.

640
00:41:42,708 --> 00:41:44,460
I wasn't close to him.

641
00:41:44,543 --> 00:41:46,962
I wasn't close to anyone…

642
00:41:47,963 --> 00:41:49,173
there.

643
00:41:50,049 --> 00:41:51,425
Private First Class Pyeon Sang-ho.

644
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:55,054
You spared Noh Tae-nam
on purpose, didn't you?

645
00:41:56,805 --> 00:41:59,350
Because Noh Tae-nam didn't harass you.

646
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:00,684
Aren't I right?

647
00:42:05,231 --> 00:42:06,857
-Prosecutor Doh.
-Yes.

648
00:42:06,941 --> 00:42:09,860
The interrogation is still going on,
so I wanted to see it here.

649
00:42:16,909 --> 00:42:18,244
That Cha Woo-in…

650
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:22,248
Private First Class Pyeon finally spoke.

651
00:42:22,998 --> 00:42:23,832
Did he?

652
00:42:26,752 --> 00:42:30,756
The surviving soldiers stated
that there wasn't any cruelty at all.

653
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:33,092
They said everyone was nice to you.

654
00:42:33,926 --> 00:42:35,511
You said that…

655
00:42:36,345 --> 00:42:39,473
the motive for crime doesn't matter
at the last interrogation, right?

656
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:42,184
And that everything you say
will be nothing but an excuse.

657
00:42:54,029 --> 00:42:55,155
Your mother…

658
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:58,826
will not think of your words as an excuse.

659
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:02,371
If you don't say anything,

660
00:43:02,454 --> 00:43:03,914
then your mother…

661
00:43:03,998 --> 00:43:05,708
has to live as a mother of…

662
00:43:06,542 --> 00:43:08,419
a brutal killer for the rest of her life.

663
00:43:30,399 --> 00:43:31,692
There was

664
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:32,735
cruelty.

665
00:43:40,534 --> 00:43:43,912
At first, Sergeant Ma
and only a few of them did it,

666
00:43:45,247 --> 00:43:48,959
but the more I put up with it,
the more soldiers joined to harass me,

667
00:43:50,169 --> 00:43:51,837
and even those who didn't harass me

668
00:43:52,713 --> 00:43:56,050
laughed at me and ignored me
when they saw me.

669
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:02,556
The GOP Commander and the Vice
GOP Commander were the same, too.

670
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:05,392
They were all devils.

671
00:44:06,018 --> 00:44:07,728
It was like hell every day,

672
00:44:08,437 --> 00:44:10,147
and I was so scared that

673
00:44:12,107 --> 00:44:13,233
another day was coming.

674
00:44:29,291 --> 00:44:31,418
We got his testimony
thanks to those glasses.

675
00:44:31,502 --> 00:44:35,047
The abuse in the platoon
was indeed the cause.

676
00:44:35,130 --> 00:44:37,049
Once Pyeon's trial is over,

677
00:44:37,132 --> 00:44:39,885
we should start investigating
the acts of abuse.

678
00:44:39,968 --> 00:44:42,513
I'm sure they acted as a group
to cover it up.

679
00:44:42,596 --> 00:44:44,807
Everyone involved must be punished.

680
00:44:44,890 --> 00:44:46,433
The problem is…

681
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:49,103
the survivors all have the same story.

682
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:52,314
It means it'll be hard
to get their testimonies.

683
00:44:52,398 --> 00:44:55,651
Still, there's a chance

684
00:44:55,734 --> 00:44:57,736
one of those witnesses
may change his mind.

685
00:44:58,779 --> 00:44:59,863
One of the witnesses?

686
00:44:59,947 --> 00:45:03,242
The Ministry of National Defense
is going to hold a joint funeral

687
00:45:03,325 --> 00:45:06,453
for the 13 soldiers of
the 4th Infantry Division who were killed

688
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:08,872
in the mass shooting at its GOP.

689
00:45:11,041 --> 00:45:13,168
Whatever accidents occur in here,

690
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:20,509
they will suspect you first.

691
00:45:21,093 --> 00:45:22,469
Because you are…

692
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:25,097
Noh Tae-nam, a troublemaker soldier.

693
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,900
That doggone bastard.

694
00:45:39,653 --> 00:45:41,738
Tae-nam, why did you curse like that?

695
00:45:42,865 --> 00:45:44,783
I'm pissed off,
so don't make things worse.

696
00:45:45,284 --> 00:45:47,077
Hey, even if we're angry,

697
00:45:47,619 --> 00:45:49,496
let's never compare them to dogs.

698
00:45:51,081 --> 00:45:54,418
Sergeant Ahn and Sergeant Ma
are just pieces of garbage.

699
00:45:56,211 --> 00:45:57,463
That's what I think.

700
00:45:58,046 --> 00:46:00,174
I think dogs are way better than humans.

701
00:46:00,674 --> 00:46:02,468
Dogs are not greedy and they're nice.

702
00:46:02,551 --> 00:46:04,928
But humans are greedy and selfish.

703
00:46:06,263 --> 00:46:09,224
They're all mean as hell,
like the superiors here.

704
00:46:09,975 --> 00:46:12,311
To a human, a dog is just
a part of his or her life,

705
00:46:12,394 --> 00:46:14,480
but to a dog, a human is everything.

706
00:46:16,398 --> 00:46:17,316
You're right.

707
00:46:17,983 --> 00:46:20,527
Bolt is my family. My only family.

708
00:46:21,111 --> 00:46:23,947
We the dog lovers must never

709
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:26,408
use the word "doggone"
when we curse, okay?

710
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:29,745
Yes, sir.

711
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:32,539
Never.

712
00:46:36,502 --> 00:46:37,336
Let's go.

713
00:46:39,254 --> 00:46:40,088
Hurry.

714
00:46:43,550 --> 00:46:46,428
The Army is going to hold
a casualty judging committee

715
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:49,973
to give the victims
posthumous honors and promotions…

716
00:46:50,057 --> 00:46:53,644
Hey, that means they're going
to give us compensation, right?

717
00:46:53,727 --> 00:46:56,313
-Wow, really?
-See? They are.

718
00:46:56,396 --> 00:46:58,023
We're on!

719
00:46:58,106 --> 00:46:59,608
You look more handsome on TV!

720
00:46:59,691 --> 00:47:02,236
-But I'm a patient.
-My leg.

721
00:47:04,196 --> 00:47:05,781
Won't they give us a million won?

722
00:47:05,864 --> 00:47:07,699
The government won't give us just that.

723
00:47:07,783 --> 00:47:09,326
I'm guessing 20 million, at least.

724
00:47:09,409 --> 00:47:11,954
Yes, we worked hard for this country.

725
00:47:12,037 --> 00:47:14,873
-I think I'm still in pain.
-Stop making a fuss. Take that.

726
00:47:14,957 --> 00:47:16,083
It really hurts.

727
00:47:21,505 --> 00:47:23,882
Even if we put Noh Tae-nam
in the witness' seat,

728
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:25,259
nothing's going to change.

729
00:47:25,968 --> 00:47:26,802
I know.

730
00:47:27,970 --> 00:47:31,807
For this trial,
the verdict isn't the important part.

731
00:47:34,434 --> 00:47:38,230
Have you worked on
a hard case like this before?

732
00:47:39,898 --> 00:47:41,149
This is my first time, too.

733
00:47:45,404 --> 00:47:49,032
The soldiers are the victims.
We must never forget that.

734
00:47:50,284 --> 00:47:51,118
Yes, sir.

735
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:55,914
This is a case where the victims become
the perpetrators and the other way around.

736
00:47:57,332 --> 00:48:03,046
No one can be victorious in this trial,
so it seems even more difficult.

737
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:08,844
Today, the trial
for the mass shooting at a GOP

738
00:48:08,927 --> 00:48:11,263
is going to be held at the military court.

739
00:48:11,346 --> 00:48:13,890
It's been told
that he was indicted for murder

740
00:48:13,974 --> 00:48:15,684
and other charges as well,

741
00:48:15,767 --> 00:48:18,520
therefore everyone's curious
about what the verdict will be

742
00:48:18,604 --> 00:48:20,230
for Private First Class Pyeon.

743
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:24,610
Was there any cruelty in the GOP platoon?

744
00:48:25,944 --> 00:48:28,030
How were things between the soldiers?

745
00:48:29,615 --> 00:48:30,699
How are your injuries?

746
00:48:30,782 --> 00:48:32,075
Please say something!

747
00:49:14,993 --> 00:49:17,204
Military Prosecution,
please testify everything.

748
00:49:17,287 --> 00:49:19,998
THE TRIAL FOR THE MASS SHOOTING
AT A GOP IN THE 4TH DIVISION

749
00:49:28,882 --> 00:49:32,803
The incident started when the defendant,
who was on guard duty,

750
00:49:32,886 --> 00:49:35,180
started to assault the superior
who was with him.

751
00:49:35,806 --> 00:49:37,140
You bastard!

752
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:44,940
After that,

753
00:49:45,023 --> 00:49:47,734
he took a grenade and a gun,
went to the barracks,

754
00:49:48,652 --> 00:49:52,114
and threw the grenade
at the soldiers who were in the lounge.

755
00:49:52,197 --> 00:49:55,117
He's good at being electrocuted.
He's good at that, at least.

756
00:49:59,162 --> 00:50:03,041
After that, he wandered around
in the corridor and shot the soldiers,

757
00:50:11,341 --> 00:50:14,845
and killed the soldiers
who were sleeping in the barrack.

758
00:50:14,928 --> 00:50:16,763
You guys are no different!

759
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:24,396
And finally, he shot
Sergeant Ma Beom-rak once,

760
00:50:24,479 --> 00:50:25,731
who was in the restroom,

761
00:50:25,814 --> 00:50:30,360
was surrounded by MP forces, and was
arrested while assaulting Sergeant Ma.

762
00:50:31,528 --> 00:50:32,863
Drop your gun!

763
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:40,912
A total of 13 people died,

764
00:50:40,996 --> 00:50:43,623
and many of the injured
platoon members are being treated.

765
00:50:43,707 --> 00:50:46,293
Therefore, the prosecution
indicted the defendant

766
00:50:46,376 --> 00:50:49,254
for seven charges
written on the indictment,

767
00:50:49,337 --> 00:50:52,966
including a murder of a superior,
according to the Military Criminal Act.

768
00:50:54,217 --> 00:50:56,970
The defendant's party.
Do you admit all of your indictments?

769
00:50:57,053 --> 00:50:59,473
He admits to all of his indictments.

770
00:50:59,973 --> 00:51:03,560
But he claims that his motive
was cruelty in the military.

771
00:51:04,978 --> 00:51:07,647
Military Prosecution,
were you aware of this?

772
00:51:08,523 --> 00:51:09,357
Yes.

773
00:51:09,858 --> 00:51:12,944
We secured the defendant's
testimony during the investigation.

774
00:51:13,737 --> 00:51:18,200
But all of the surviving soldiers
are denying any cruelty.

775
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:21,870
But I agree that the facts
on the motive and reasons

776
00:51:21,953 --> 00:51:23,789
for his crime need to be confirmed.

777
00:51:25,373 --> 00:51:28,084
Therefore, I summon
the surviving soldiers as witnesses.

778
00:51:31,463 --> 00:51:34,716
The surviving soldiers,
please sit in the witness seats.

779
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,301
An oath.

780
00:51:37,260 --> 00:51:39,513
I solemnly swear
that I will tell the whole truth,

781
00:51:39,596 --> 00:51:41,056
and nothing but the truth,

782
00:51:41,139 --> 00:51:44,434
and if I tell a lie,
I will accept punishment for perjury.

783
00:51:58,490 --> 00:52:00,617
Was there any form of cruelty

784
00:52:00,700 --> 00:52:04,037
that took place in the GOP platoon
before the mass shooting occurred?

785
00:52:13,755 --> 00:52:16,174
There wasn't…

786
00:52:16,258 --> 00:52:17,467
any abuse.

787
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:22,180
That makes no sense.

788
00:52:22,264 --> 00:52:24,057
There wasn't any abuse.

789
00:52:24,140 --> 00:52:25,892
There was none.

790
00:52:25,976 --> 00:52:27,269
No, absolutely not.

791
00:52:27,352 --> 00:52:29,229
He was guarding the battlefront with me,

792
00:52:29,312 --> 00:52:31,273
and he suddenly murmured
like some crazy guy,

793
00:52:31,356 --> 00:52:33,275
saying that he should go kill Sergeant Ma,

794
00:52:33,358 --> 00:52:35,277
then knocked me out
and deserted from duty.

795
00:52:36,194 --> 00:52:37,320
Pyeon committed

796
00:52:37,404 --> 00:52:40,448
the mass shooting
because he went totally mad.

797
00:52:40,532 --> 00:52:42,701
When a soldier of concern
like Pyeon comes,

798
00:52:42,784 --> 00:52:44,578
the superiors have a really tough time.

799
00:52:45,203 --> 00:52:48,081
Since he came to the GOP,
he couldn't adapt, he was left out,

800
00:52:48,164 --> 00:52:49,708
and he suffered from insomnia,

801
00:52:49,791 --> 00:52:51,793
so I let him sleep next to me,
gave him advice,

802
00:52:51,877 --> 00:52:53,420
and took good care of him.

803
00:52:53,503 --> 00:52:57,132
But it seems like he felt
that was harassment.

804
00:52:58,174 --> 00:53:00,093
I only cared for
Private First Class Pyeon.

805
00:53:01,136 --> 00:53:02,429
You have no idea

806
00:53:02,512 --> 00:53:05,682
how nice our platoon members
were to Private First Class Pyeon.

807
00:53:06,308 --> 00:53:08,310
But he shot those who were nice to him…

808
00:53:08,393 --> 00:53:10,186
He did that to those innocent…

809
00:53:10,270 --> 00:53:11,479
There wasn't abuse.

810
00:53:11,563 --> 00:53:12,522
Absolutely not.

811
00:53:12,606 --> 00:53:13,773
There wasn't.

812
00:53:13,857 --> 00:53:15,775
There wasn't any abuse.

813
00:53:15,859 --> 00:53:18,069
That's the way for me
to keep this position.

814
00:53:19,070 --> 00:53:22,449
All of the criticism must go
to Private First Class Pyeon.

815
00:53:32,417 --> 00:53:35,045
When I become a sergeant,
I will get rid of all of these,

816
00:53:35,128 --> 00:53:37,589
so wait until then.

817
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:40,967
It's okay even if you say the same thing.

818
00:53:42,135 --> 00:53:43,720
I'm okay, Tae-nam.

819
00:53:44,596 --> 00:53:46,598
No, you're not okay.

820
00:53:48,683 --> 00:53:50,352
If you were going to put up with it,

821
00:53:51,478 --> 00:53:53,229
you should've done it until the end…

822
00:53:55,065 --> 00:53:58,026
That Private First Class Pyeon
isn't a serviceperson!

823
00:53:58,944 --> 00:54:01,321
No, he's not even human!

824
00:54:07,327 --> 00:54:08,828
There was abuse.

825
00:54:14,250 --> 00:54:15,210
Witness.

826
00:54:16,002 --> 00:54:17,128
What did you just say?

827
00:54:19,089 --> 00:54:20,715
Private Noh Tae-nam.

828
00:54:20,799 --> 00:54:22,801
You abused him, you bastard!

829
00:54:26,638 --> 00:54:28,098
This is wrong!

830
00:54:28,181 --> 00:54:30,183
This really is wrong!

831
00:54:30,266 --> 00:54:31,309
Don't you think?

832
00:54:31,393 --> 00:54:33,895
You guys didn't come
to the military to do this.

833
00:54:37,399 --> 00:54:38,566
You…

834
00:54:41,528 --> 00:54:43,947
Sang-ho, you should be
punished for shooting people,

835
00:54:45,448 --> 00:54:47,701
and all of you, who made him shoot people,

836
00:54:48,451 --> 00:54:50,120
should get punished, too.

837
00:54:53,873 --> 00:54:55,667
Why am I saying this?

838
00:54:56,292 --> 00:54:57,127
Right.

839
00:54:57,627 --> 00:55:00,505
I know I don't have any right
to say this, but…

840
00:55:01,381 --> 00:55:02,757
this is wrong.

841
00:55:04,426 --> 00:55:06,136
This is just so wrong!

842
00:55:06,219 --> 00:55:08,263
Witness, watch your language.

843
00:55:10,557 --> 00:55:11,558
Mother.

844
00:55:12,350 --> 00:55:14,144
No, Division Commander Noh Hwa-young.

845
00:55:15,186 --> 00:55:18,523
Mother, you forced me to commit perjury
so you can keep that uniform on.

846
00:55:19,190 --> 00:55:21,276
Witness, please be seated!

847
00:55:21,359 --> 00:55:23,361
Is this the military you want to make?

848
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:25,697
Answer me!

849
00:55:27,157 --> 00:55:29,200
Is this the military you want to make?

850
00:55:29,701 --> 00:55:30,785
Military police!

851
00:55:30,869 --> 00:55:33,038
Get the witness
out of the court, right now!

852
00:55:33,121 --> 00:55:34,873
Answer me!

853
00:55:34,956 --> 00:55:36,708
Please answer me!

854
00:55:36,791 --> 00:55:39,210
Please! Please answer me!

855
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:54,434
Defendant.

856
00:55:55,935 --> 00:55:58,313
Do you have any final words
you want to say?

857
00:56:01,107 --> 00:56:03,943
It's all my fault.

858
00:56:05,987 --> 00:56:09,115
It's my fault for not being able
to put up with it a bit more.

859
00:56:13,787 --> 00:56:16,706
It's my fault for not being able
to put up with it until the end.

860
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:25,131
I'm sorry.

861
00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:29,344
I'm really sorry.

862
00:56:45,026 --> 00:56:48,238
One soldier suffered from endless cruelty.

863
00:56:49,364 --> 00:56:53,118
And because of that, a horrendous tragedy
that cannot be undone has occurred.

864
00:56:54,536 --> 00:56:58,164
Most cases of violence within a group
are covered up with silence.

865
00:56:58,665 --> 00:57:01,626
And those curtains of silence
are usually opened

866
00:57:01,709 --> 00:57:04,504
after a tragic incident.

867
00:57:05,797 --> 00:57:08,842
Before the curtains opened,
the victim turned into the perpetrator,

868
00:57:10,009 --> 00:57:13,721
and after the curtains opened,
the perpetrator turned into the victim.

869
00:57:17,851 --> 00:57:21,020
As a military prosecutor
in charge of this case,

870
00:57:21,604 --> 00:57:25,024
I really wanted to avoid
this most painful moment.

871
00:57:26,734 --> 00:57:28,611
But now,

872
00:57:28,695 --> 00:57:34,617
I will do my duty as a military prosecutor
who must judge justice for the people.

873
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:39,747
Murder cannot be justified for any reason.

874
00:57:43,751 --> 00:57:44,919
Therefore, I request you

875
00:57:45,003 --> 00:57:48,840
to sentence Private First Class
Pyeon Sang-ho, the defendant,

876
00:57:48,923 --> 00:57:52,051
the maximum sentence, which is death.

877
00:58:04,355 --> 00:58:05,982
Based on the overall situation,

878
00:58:06,983 --> 00:58:10,612
it is inevitable to sentence the defendant
to the maximum sentence.

879
00:58:11,279 --> 00:58:12,697
I hereby sentence the verdict.

880
00:58:13,656 --> 00:58:14,574
The verdict.

881
00:58:15,158 --> 00:58:17,994
The court sentences
the defendant to death.

882
00:58:21,873 --> 00:58:22,999
Sang-ho!

883
00:58:25,084 --> 00:58:27,837
Sang-ho!

884
00:58:29,797 --> 00:58:31,174
Sang-ho!

885
00:58:31,257 --> 00:58:33,051
No! Sang-ho! My son!

886
00:59:00,620 --> 00:59:02,664
I delivered the new glasses you gave me

887
00:59:03,873 --> 00:59:06,000
to Private First Class Pyeon.

888
00:59:06,584 --> 00:59:08,419
I didn't want him to have blurry vision…

889
00:59:09,837 --> 00:59:11,631
during his long trip.

890
00:59:13,007 --> 00:59:14,634
So I wanted to give them to him.

891
00:59:20,348 --> 00:59:21,724
Military Prosecutor.

892
00:59:23,142 --> 00:59:27,897
Thank you for granting my last wish.

893
00:59:59,512 --> 01:00:01,055
You do the briefing.

894
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:03,558
You want me to do it?

895
01:00:04,934 --> 01:00:06,811
I dealt with this trial

896
01:00:06,894 --> 01:00:09,397
coldly throughout,

897
01:00:09,981 --> 01:00:11,149
but you…

898
01:00:12,692 --> 01:00:14,444
Pyeon Sang-ho and Noh Tae-nam.

899
01:00:15,528 --> 01:00:18,156
You didn't give up
on the perpetrator and the victim.

900
01:00:20,158 --> 01:00:21,326
You do it.

901
01:00:24,996 --> 01:00:25,913
Yes, sir.

902
01:00:32,754 --> 01:00:33,880
Please say something.

903
01:00:33,963 --> 01:00:35,131
Please say something.

904
01:00:35,673 --> 01:00:39,636
The investigation will begin for all
soldiers who were involved in the cruelty

905
01:00:39,719 --> 01:00:42,472
and all of those who participated

906
01:00:42,555 --> 01:00:45,058
in reducing and covering up this case.

907
01:00:45,141 --> 01:00:47,560
And we will also thoroughly investigate

908
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:50,188
Division Commander Noh Hwa-young's
alleged attempt

909
01:00:50,271 --> 01:00:54,525
to force someone into committing perjury,
which was mentioned during the trial.

910
01:01:12,377 --> 01:01:14,671
Starting with investigating
Division Commander Noh,

911
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:18,049
we will begin investigations
on the colossal military corruption gate

912
01:01:18,132 --> 01:01:19,759
suspected for a long time.

913
01:01:21,511 --> 01:01:22,720
Get started.

914
01:01:48,871 --> 01:01:51,082
We will now begin a search and seizure

915
01:01:51,165 --> 01:01:53,459
for failing to frustrate
crimes of subordinates.

916
01:01:54,252 --> 01:01:56,796
Do as you wish,
Doh Bae-man and Cha Woo-in.

917
01:01:58,923 --> 01:02:01,759
But you'll have to deal
with the aftermath.

918
01:02:02,385 --> 01:02:03,553
No, you'll have to

919
01:02:03,636 --> 01:02:05,888
deal with the aftermath,
Division Commander.

